Privacy Policy
Updated August 2022
Introduction
BibleProject respects your privacy and is committed to safeguarding your sensitive information. This privacy notice (“
Privacy Notice
”) is an agreement between you and BibleProject and its affiliates, corporate parent(s), and subsidiaries (collectively “
BibleProject
”, “
us
”, “
our
,” or “
we
”) while accessing and using our products or services, including our websites (including bibleproject.com), social media pages, channels, related applications across any devices and platforms, online classroom programs (such as
Classroom
), learning management systems (such as
Learn.Bible
), and any other BP online presence (collectively, the “Services”), and is governed by and part of BibleProject’s
Terms of Use
.
Personal Information
As used in this Privacy Notice, “Personal Information” means information that specifically identifies an individual (e.g. a name, address, telephone number, e-mail address, username, or credit card number), or information about that individual that is directly linked to personally identifiable information. Personal Information does not include (a) aggregate information, meaning data we collect about your use of the Services or about a group or category of services or users, from which individual identities or other Personal Information has been removed or (b) deidentified information that cannot be easily linked back to the individual.
This Privacy Notice describes our practices for collecting, using, maintaining, protecting, and disclosing your Personal Information, as well as Personal Information we collect as a result of your interactions with BibleProject via telephone, through mail, or in person at our physical locations.
Please read this notice carefully to understand our policies and practices regarding your information and how we will treat it.
Consent
By accessing or using the Services, creating a BibleProject user profile, visiting our studio, or submitting Personal Information to BibleProject, you consent to this Privacy Notice and the collection and use of your Personal Information as described below. If you do not agree with our policies and practices, you may not be able to access or benefit from certain portions of the Services.
Scope
Please be advised that this Privacy Notice applies to information that we collect:
when you access or use the Services.
when you visit our studio.
when you submit your information to us.
when you create or use a user profile.
when we communicate with you through email and other means.
through third parties that we work with to provide our services.
by any other means over the course of your access or use of the Services.
This Privacy Notice does not apply to information collected about you in any other way, including through mobile applications, content, or websites not operated by BibleProject.
Lawful Basis
We will only collect your Personal Information (a) when applicable, with your consent or (b) if we have a legitimate interest in doing so. If we collect or use your Personal Information based on your consent, we will also notify you of any changes and request your further consent as needed.
Children's Privacy
BibleProject recognizes the need to provide further privacy protections with respect to Personal Information of children. We do not knowingly collect any Personal Information from children under 16 without obtaining consent from the child’s parent or guardian. Generally, registration for BibleProject Services is only available to those age 16 or older. If a child under age 16 wishes to register on the Services, and the BibleProject service permits registration for a child under age 16 (currently only Learn.Bible), BibleProject requires the child’s parent or guardian provide consent for the registration via our email confirmation process before we activate the child’s registration. If BibleProject does not receive parental or guardian consent within 24 hours of the child’s registration request, we will delete any Personal Information the child may have provided to us as part of their registration request. If you are under 16 and your parent or guardian has not completed our registration and consent process, BibleProject instructs you to not use the Services, including its interactive or public comment features, make purchases or donations through the Services, or otherwise provide BibleProject with any Personal Information.
BibleProject is a 501(c)(3) nonprofit corporation and therefore is exempt from the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act. Nevertheless, BibleProject values the privacy of children who may find our content informational. All the provisions of this Privacy Notice apply to all users of the Services, including children. Younger visitors should always check with their parents or guardians before sharing information on any website or mobile application, and we encourage families to discuss their household guidelines regarding the online sharing of Personal Information.
If you believe that BibleProject may have information from or about a child under 16 without parent or guardian consent, or if you wish to review or request deletion of the Personal Information BibleProject has about your child, please contact us at
legal@bibleproject.com
or toll free at (855) 700-9109.
How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
When you access or use our Services or visit our studio, we collect certain Personal Information from you. We collect this information:
Directly from you when you provide it to us.
Automatically as you navigate the Services.
From third parties, including third-party websites.
Please note that some offers, services, and portions of our Services may only be accessible to you if you register with us. You are welcome to limit the information you provide to us to the minimum necessary to receive our services, and you can
contact BibleProject
at any time to edit the information we have about you. Please note, however, that if you refuse to give us your Personal Information, or later withdraw your consent, we most likely will not be able to communicate with you or provide you with our services.
Information You Provide to Us.
We collect Personal Information directly from you with your consent when you visit our studio in person or interact with us on the Services. The Personal Information you provide to us may include:
Contact Information
- We collect information that you provide by filling out electronic forms on our Services. This may include your name, age, telephone number, e-mail address, address, and other personally identifiable information. We may use this information to register you to use our Services, verify if you are a child under age 16, send you newsletters, and otherwise provide you with information, products and services.
User Generated Material
- Our Services may include features that permit you to post written content, photos, videos, or other content, subject to our Terms of Use. It is your decision whether to use these features and any information or content you post is provided by you voluntarily. We may keep records and copies of your correspondence (including email addresses), if you post User Generated Material or contact us.
Payment Information
- You can make donations to us in various ways. We use PCI compliant third-party payment processors (such as
Stripe
and
Paypal
) and other third-parties (such as
Google Pay
,
Apple Pay
, and
Patreon
) to handle most online transactions, including credit card payments and ACH transfers. You may be prompted by these third parties to provide credit card, bank account, or other payment information needed to facilitate your donation. We do not collect, process, or store payment information provided to third parties, but we may keep a record of transactions you carry out through our Services and to ensure that the donation is used for the purpose you request.
When you send us personal checks or gift us stocks, bonds, or mutual funds, we may collect, process, or store payment information provided to ensure that the donation is used for the purpose you request and to provide you with documentation needed to itemize your donation for tax purposes or your personal use. If we have trouble processing a donation, we will use your contact information to contact you.
In-Person Information
- When you visit BibleProject’s studio, we will also ask you to complete a visitor intake form and we may capture your image using onsite cameras when you enter or exit the building or the studio space. We collect this information to ensure the security of our staff and visitors. Also, depending on the purpose of your visit, we may ask you to complete additional forms. We will notify you of our purpose for these forms at the time of collection.
Information We Collect Through Automatic Data Collection Technologies.
As you navigate and interact with our Services, we may use automatic data collection technologies like website analytics to collect certain information about your equipment, browsing actions, and patterns. We collect this information to achieve our legitimate interests of maintaining and improving the Services and measuring our outreach and marketing efforts. The information we collect through automatic data collection technologies includes:
Log Files
- We collect anonymous and technical information from your computer, including traffic data, location data, logs, and other communication data and the resources that you access and use on the Services. We also collect information about your computer, device, and internet connection, including your IP address, operating system, device type, and browser type. We anonymize this information so it does not identify you and use it to monitor user behavior. We also use this information to estimate our audience size and usage patterns, store information about your preferences, customize your user experience, speed up search response times and recognize you when you return to our Services. These analytics help us to improve our Services and to deliver a better and more personalized service
Emails
- Our emails contain an embedded tracking code to keep track of when the recipient receives and opens the email and when the recipient visits our Services via a link in the email.
Cookies
- Like most commercial websites, we use cookies to track use of our Services. Please read our
Cookie Notice
for more information about how we use cookies.
The information we collect automatically may include Personal Information, or we may maintain the information or associate it with Personal Information we collect in other ways or receive from third parties. This information may also be merged into aggregate information about site visitors and traffic. If you do not wish to have BibleProject collect and use your anonymous and technical information as described in this paragraph, immediately stop using the Services, or contact us as described under “
Controlling Your Personal Information
."
BibleProject tracks the number of users who come to our Services from social networking sites (e.g., Facebook, YouTube or Twitter) to achieve our legitimate interest of measuring the effectiveness of our social media ads and posts. If you access our Services from a social networking site, or if you otherwise agree to associate your account with us with a social networking site, we may also receive Personal Information about you from such social networking site. Please note that social media sites from which we may receive your Personal Information are not controlled or supervised by BibleProject. Any questions regarding how the social media site collects or processes your Personal Information should be directed to the social media site provider. We may retain this information with the information we collect from you directly.
Other Ways We May Use Your Information
We may also use Personal Information that we collect from you or about you:
To develop and improve our products and services.
To present our Services and its contents to you.
To provide you with information, products, or services that you request from us.
To fulfill any other purpose for which you provide it.
To carry out our obligations and enforce our rights arising from any contracts entered into between you and us, including for billing and collection.
To notify you about changes to our Services or any products or services we offer or provide through it.
To allow you to participate in interactive features on our Services.
To protect your privacy and enforce this Privacy Notice.
To protect our rights and property.
If we believe it is necessary to identify, contact, or bring legal action against persons or entities who may be causing injury to you, to BibleProject, or to others, or to comply with a law, regulation, legal process or court order.
In any other way we may describe when you provide the information.
For any other purpose with your consent.
BibleProject may use a cookie or third party web beacon to collect and analyze your Personal Information or your activities on the Services (e.g., click stream information, browser type, time and date, subject clicked or scrolled over) to help identify advertisements or offers that may be of interest to you. If you prefer BibleProject to not use information based on your online behavior to provide you with tailored content and advertising, you may opt out of online behavioral advertising by following the instructions in
Opting Out of Communications
.
We may combine information we collect about you through the Services with other information about you that we receive from third-party sources. By way of example and not limitation, we may use a change of address or other list service to ensure that our records for your account are accurate.
Disclosure of Your Information
BibleProject will not sell your Personal Information to any third parties.
We may disclose Personal Information that we collect or you provide as described in this Privacy Notice:
To our subsidiaries and affiliates.
To contractors, payment processors, service providers, and other third parties we use to support our business.
To a buyer or other successor in the event of a merger, divestiture, restructuring, reorganization, dissolution, or other sale or transfer of some or all of BibleProject’s assets, whether as a going concern or as part of bankruptcy, liquidation, or similar proceeding, in which Personal Information held by BibleProject about users of our Services is among the assets transferred.
To our advertising and analytics partners, such as Google Analytics. The privacy notice of these third party companies applies to their collection, use and disclosure of your information. These third parties may combine your information with the information of other consumers for purposes of conducting these studies and/or analytics. For more information, please visit Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on.
To fulfill the purpose for which you provide it. For example, if you give us an email address to use the “email a friend” feature of our Services, we will transmit the contents of that email and your email address to the recipients.
For any other purpose disclosed by us when you provide the information.
With your consent.
We may also disclose your Personal Information:
To comply with any court order, law, or legal process, including to respond to any government or regulatory request.
To enforce or apply our Terms of Use and other agreements, including for billing and collection purposes.
If we believe disclosure is necessary or appropriate to protect the rights, property, or safety of BibleProject, our customers, or others.
Aggregate Information
We may share aggregate or de-identified information without restriction. The information we share will not identify you personally. However, it is possible that third parties may be able to combine this aggregate information with other data they have about you, or that they receive from other third parties, in a manner that allows them to identify you personally.
Controlling Your Personal Information
If you are a resident of the European Union, you have certain additional rights in relation to your Personal Information. You can exercise these rights, express concerns, or obtain additional information about the use of your Personal Information by contacting us toll free at (855) 700-9109 or by email at
legal@bibleproject.com
.
