What this means for you
What you can do
Be informed about how your Personal Information will be processed.
We will inform you via this Privacy Notice about how we will use your Personal Information, for what purposes and who else might have access to it.
Please read this Privacy Notice carefully and contact us if you have any questions.
Access your Personal Information.
Upon request, we will provide you with access to the Personal Information we have about you, meaning the categories of information we have about you, how we collect it, how we use it, and who has access to it.
You can request that we provide you with a copy of the Personal Information that we process about you. In some cases, we may be legally permitted or required to refuse part or all of a request for access.
Prevent processing of your Personal Information in certain circumstances.
We will, in certain circumstances and to the extent required by law, restrict our processing of your Personal Information.
You can request that we restrict processing of your Personal Information if (i) the Personal Information is inaccurate, (ii) the processing is unlawful, (iii) we no longer need the Personal Information, or (iv) you exercise your right to object (see below).
Rectify the Personal Information we have about you.
We are required to take steps to ensure the accuracy of the Personal Information that we process.
If you discover that the Personal Information that we hold about you is incorrect or if your Personal Information changes (e.g. a name or address change), please let us know and we will update our records.
Data portability.
In some circumstances, we will be required to transfer your Personal Information to another organization at your request.
You have the right to request that we transfer the Personal Information we have about you to another organization in a structured, commonly used machine-readable format.
Erasure of your Personal Information (aka "right to be forgotten").
In certain circumstances and where we are required to do so by law, we must delete the Personal Information we hold about you at your request. This right is not absolute. It is likely that there will be scenarios where we are not obligated to comply with your request.
You have the right to request that we delete your Personal Information. If you make this request, we will need to balance certain legal, contractual, and business interests against your right to request the deletion of the relevant Personal Information.
Object to certain processing of your Personal Information.
If you object to our processing of your Personal Information, we will consider certain legal, contractual and business interests and obligations and balance these against your right to object to the processing.
You may object to the processing of your Personal Information in certain circumstances. You can also object to our use of your Personal Information for direct marketing purposes.
Not to be subject to decisions made solely via automated processing (i.e. a decision made about you by a computer or algorithm without human intervention).
In certain circumstances, we must give you the right to object to decisions we make by automated processing. We are also required to keep records of our automated data processing practices and provide information about the way that these decisions are made.
You may object to a decision made by automated processing if it was made wholly by a computer or algorithm without human input.
We will fulfill your request to exercise any of these rights within 30 days of receiving a complete request. You also have the right to correct any errors contained in that information. Please note that BibleProject is required by law to verify your identity before fulfilling your request, which may include collecting additional Personal Information from you.
By mail at BibleProject 501 SE 14th Avenue Portland, OR 97214
California Privacy Rights
Because BibleProject is not organized or operated for the profit or financial benefit of its shareholders or other owners, we are exempt from compliance with the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018, as amended by the California Privacy Rights Act of 2020 (collectively, the “CCPA”). However, some of our contracts with service providers and other third parties may require us to comply with the CCPA. Users of our Services who are California residents may have certain rights related to their Personal Information, such as the right to (a) receive information describing the categories of Personal Information about you that we have collected, and whether that information was sold to a third party; (b) receive a list of categories of third parties with which we have shared your Personal Information; (c) if we sell your Personal Information, instruct us to not sell your Personal Information to third parties; and (d) receive equal service regardless if you exercise your privacy rights.
Additionally, California Civil Code sections 1798.83-1798.84 entitles California residents to ask us for a notice that identifies the categories of Personal Information we share with affiliates and/or third parties for marketing purposes, and provides contact information for such affiliates and/or third parties.
If you are a California resident and you would like to request a copy of this Privacy Notice or exercise the rights available to you under applicable California law, please call us toll free at (855) 700-9109 or send us an email at
legal@bibleproject.com
with the subject line “Request for California Privacy Information.”
Opting Out of Communications
We want to communicate with you only if you want to hear from us. You can modify or limit the communications BibleProject sends to you by clicking the “Preferences” or “Unsubscribe” link at the bottom of any of our emails. You may also contact us directly toll free at (855) 700-9109 or by email at
legal@bibleproject.com
. Please be sure to include your full name, email address, mailing address, and specifically what information you do not want to receive. If you like, you may use one of the following statements in your message to us:
I prefer not to receive email advertisements, such as updates regarding products and services, special promotions, or upcoming events.
I prefer not to receive direct mail advertisements, such as periodic catalogs and mailings regarding products and services, special promotions, or upcoming events.
Do Not Track Signals
Do Not Track is a privacy preference that users can set in their web browsers. When a user turns on the Do Not Track signal, the browser sends a message to websites requesting them not to track the user. For information about Do Not Track, visit
www.allaboutdnt.org
. At this time, bibleproject.com does not respond to Do Not Track browser settings or signals. In addition, we may use other technology that is standard to the internet to track visitors to our websites. Those tools may be used by us and by third parties to collect information about you and your internet activity, even if you have turned on the Do Not Track signal.
U.S. Privacy Laws
The Services are owned and operated in the United States. If you access the Services from outside of the United States, any information that we collect about you will be transferred to servers inside the United States. The privacy laws in the United States may not be as protective as those in your jurisdiction. By allowing us to collect Personal Information about you, you consent to such transfer and processing of your Personal Information as described in this Privacy Notice.
Data Security
We have implemented commercially reasonable measures both online and offline to secure your Personal Information from accidental loss and from unauthorized access, use, alteration, and disclosure. We maintain physical, electronic, and procedural security measures to safeguard your non-public Personal Information. These safeguards include limiting our in-house storage of your Personal Information to Contact Information, and securing that data with industry standard encryption. Payment and financial information is hosted on a Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard compliant hosting provider. We transmit all other Personal Information to a service provider that meets international security standards via secure token for that service provider to store and maintain. We update and test our technology to improve the protection of our information about you and to assure the integrity of that information.
The safety and security of your information also depends on you. Where we have given you (or where you have chosen) a password for access to certain parts of our Services, you are responsible for keeping this password confidential. We ask you not to share your password with anyone. Also remember to log off your account and close your browser window when you have finished your visit. This is to ensure that others cannot access your account, especially if you are sharing a computer with someone else or are using a computer in a public place. All internet users should take care with how they handle and disclose their Personal Information. The User Generated Material and other information you share in public areas may be viewed by any user of the Services.
Unfortunately, the transmission of information via the internet is not completely secure. Although we do our best to protect your Personal Information, we cannot guarantee the security of your Personal Information transmitted to our Services or that unauthorized third parties will not defeat our security measures or use nonpublic Personal Information for improper purposes. Any transmission of Personal Information is at your own risk. We are not responsible for circumvention of any privacy settings or security measures contained on the Services. Please refer to the Federal Trade Commission's website for information about how to help protect yourself against identity theft.
Third Party Services & Advertising
This Privacy Notice applies only to information collected by BibleProject. We may provide links to third party websites from our Services as a service to our users, but we have no ability to control, and we are not responsible for, the privacy and data collection, use, and disclosure practices of third party websites. When you click on links that take you to external websites, you will be subject to their privacy notices and practices and not ours. We encourage you to review and understand the privacy notices of such websites before providing them with any information.
Terms of Use
The Terms of Use of our Services govern all matters not set forth in this Privacy Notice. We encourage you to familiarize yourself with our
Terms of Use
.
Changes to Our Privacy Policy
We may change this Privacy Notice from time to time to ensure its accuracy. If we make changes, the revised notice will be posted on this page. Your continued use of our Services or other services after the posting of changes to this Privacy Notice will mean you accept these changes. In some cases, we may attempt to contact you using the contact information you have provided, in order to give you choices about our using your information in a manner different from that stated at the time of collection. Please check back frequently, especially before you provide us with Personal Information, to determine the current scope of the notice.
Unauthorized Use
If you become aware of any unauthorized submission of information to BibleProject, including children’s information, please inform us by contacting us at the contact information listed below so that we may delete it.
